My coworker doesn’t understand this.

Which leads to her complaining about walking in the neighborhood every clothing shop now makes house calls.

We did go to the beach that day.

It was worth it to see her face when we put on the top.

Thankfully, we got ourselves in a state of undress, we’d already spent our host-meager cash for the day on lunch.

I got to hang out by the pool with a few friends while they swam around the not quite open pool … you really just couldn’t see the bottom of it.

In case you were wondering, it is a large playground out in the middle of nowhere, no pool, no slide, no cement to go sliding on either.

The campground does have transportation to La Flor from Managua.

And a fully self-contained laundry facility. So you are free to ramble and explore Nicaragua while your laundry slowly dries.

And there’s a couple of dogs to pet.

… is more rewarding than the rapid shuttling of people across boring, flat land.

… we mistook for a scenic rolling hillside (stupid B.)

… so our speedy journey was exciting, nothing like slowing down and stopping every 40km or so to go visit a tiny town.

I tried to explain, yes, I have lots of food in our fridge, I’m on a budget, and the produce looked … questionable. And then there was an ordeal with the salted pork.
